Description:
A true New York loft experience
Located in vibrant Oxford St, the warehouse capital of Melbourne, this stunning split level Edgard Pirrota designed warehouse loft has remained true to its NYC inspirations. A simple two level layout allows for light and lofty warehouse living blended with original features as well as modern appointment. Simply put everything you would expect from a contemporary residence! Comprises huge open plan living and delightful courtyard terrace, large kitchen area, separate laundry and downstairs powder room with upstairs accommodation by way of super-sized master bedroom with WIR's and ensuite, good sized second bedroom and purpose built study area. Other stand-out features include off street parking, security entry, hydronic heating, split system AC in bedrooms & living and data/av/tv/foxtel cabling. Moments from Gertrude, Smith & Brunswick Streets with easy CBD and public transport access close by.
Agent - hockingstuart
Michael Amarant : 0411 144 569
Insights: 7/79 Oxford Street, COLLINGWOOD VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in COLLINGWOOD have recently been sold.

Description:
Super sized apartment living...
Located in the vibrant East Melbourne fringe suburb of Collingwood this fabulous 1 bedroom apartment is super sized and ready for immediate enjoyment. Moments from Victoria, Smith, Gertrude & Brunswick St the apartment offers a brilliant lifestyle or investment opportunity. With massive open plan living area, modern kitchen, huge central bathroom, generous bedroom, amble storage with BIR, & car park you have all the boxes ticked for convenient inner city living or investment.
Easy city and public transport access plus a quick stroll to the MCG or Yarra River Parklands makes this a wonderful lock up and leave buying opportunity.

Description:
FEDERATION TO MODERN: A HOUSE OF SURPRISES
This captivating home, close to transport, leading cafes and hospitals, has been creatively renovated and extended to incorporate a spacious light-filled living and dining room, with soaring timber truss ceiling and pot belly stove, open to a solid timber kitchen and flowing to deck and private ROW- access courtyard. A functional floor plan incorporates two double bedrooms with custom BIRs and a stylish bathroom with freestanding bath and shower. Including vast loft storage and a tank-fed laundry, this warm and inviting home features polished hardwood floors, period detail, split-system air conditioning and alarm. Close to Victoria, Smith and Gertrude Streets, and just a short walk to the CBD, this is an inner-city gem!

Description:
Sensational Starter with Northern Scope
Combining Victorian charm, a deep allotment with preferred northerly rear and a quiet Collingwood position, this classic one of a pair provides a brilliant starting point for inner city living just a short stroll from the buzz of both Smith and Brunswick Streets and convenient city bound trams. Comfortably presented now, spacious 3 bedroom proportions present an instant city fringe lifestyle solution or clever investment as well as an exciting foundation for renovation/ extension (STCA) whenever desired. Nestled within a classic period streetscape with high traditional ceilings, central living with gas heater, functional kitchen, bathroom with laundry taps, alfresco entertaining and deep northern courtyard. Excellent size and scope so you'll have to be quick!

Description:
HATS OFF TO GREAT DESIGN
Live life on the edge! Live on the coolest street in the hippest suburb at Trilby on Smith Street.
Hats off to brilliant design. Your Trilby apartment is generously sized, efficiently laid out and has been created for modern day living, featuring a clever storage plan, oversized balconies and impressive views.
Share the rooftop garden with your neighbours and friends, enjoying a fully landscaped garden, outdoor kitchen facilities, Teppanyaki kitchen, dining area, sun lounges, recreational space and inspiring city views.
The Trilby interiors are chic, with the living area inspired by Collingwood itself: moody and stylish, all to ensure functionality and the latest aesthetic, and offers a range of internal finishes.
With a choice of between a classic or contemporary colour scheme, Trilby apartments feature:
Stainless steel SMEG appliances
Solid oak timber flooring
Natural wool carpets
Sophisticated track lighting
Durable scratch and stain resistant European porcelain benchtops
On-trend aged bronze tapware
Convenient and space efficient cupboard and drawers
Generous storage facilities
Convenient open shelving and functional cabinets
DISPLAY OPEN
410 Smith Street, Collingwood
11am – 5pm Daily
Or By Appointment

Description:
HATS OFF TO GREAT DESIGN
Live life on the edge! Live on the coolest street in the hippest suburb at Trilby on Smith Street.
Hats off to brilliant design. Your Trilby apartment is generously sized, efficiently laid out and has been created for modern day living, featuring a clever storage plan, oversized balconies and impressive views.
Share the rooftop garden with your neighbours and friends, enjoying a fully landscaped garden, outdoor kitchen facilities, Teppanyaki kitchen, dining area, sun lounges, recreational space and inspiring city views.
The Trilby interiors are chic, with the living area inspired by Collingwood itself: moody and stylish, all to ensure functionality and the latest aesthetic, and offers a range of internal finishes.
With a choice of between a classic or contemporary colour scheme, Trilby apartments feature:
Stainless steel SMEG appliances
Solid oak timber flooring
Natural wool carpets
Sophisticated track lighting
Durable scratch and stain resistant European porcelain benchtops
On-trend aged bronze tapware
Convenient and space efficient cupboard and drawers
Generous storage facilities
Convenient open shelving and functional cabinets
DISPLAY OPEN
410 Smith Street, Collingwood
11am – 5pm Daily
Or By Appointment

"The Ultimate Warehouse" (c1880)
Spanning over 5 luxurious levels, in the Iconic "Grain Store" Victoria Distillery, is this impressive designer showpiece.
Combining a perfect marriage of both Residential and Commercial elements, the property offers a fantastic opportunity to run your own business from home.
Boasting generous multiple living zones, the flexibility of either a 2/3 or 4 bedroom set up, 2 kitchens and 3 bathrooms.

Description:
Versatile Victorian Distillery Warehouse Conversion
An evocative European mews-style setting and classic scissor-gate entrance create a marvellous mood that extends throughout the versatile single-level spaces of this ground-floor warehouse conversion in the historic Victorian Distillery c1860. Lofty industrial ceilings, polished hardwood floors, whitewashed walls and picture windows frame the flexible open-plan layout of this remarkable long-held residence designed to adapt to your lifestyle desires of easy living, working and entertaining. Located in Collingwood's arts/fashion quarter near Gertrude and Smiths Streets, Fitzroy Gardens and the city; the floorplan features 4 principal rooms, large fully-appointed kitchen, huge mosaic-tiled bathroom, separate laundry, gas heating, store room, private entry/alfresco area and parking for 1 car. Note: Commercial 2 zoning.

Description:
POSITION PLUS POTENTIAL. ADD VALUE!
This freestanding Victorian offers wonderful investment and renovation scope, but can be enjoyed right now. In this highly sought after Collingwood position, the property is close to Smith Street and Brunswick Street cafes, Queens Parade and entrance to the Eastern freeway. The classic floor plan incorporates two double bedrooms from a wide hallway, spacious light-filled living and dining areas, an updated kitchen with generous storage, bathroom with overbath shower, laundry and separate WC. Opening to the rear is a sunny private garden. Features include gas heating, air-conditioning and period detail.

Exceptional living, exclusive setting
GARRA - one of Collingwood's best boutique developments finds this fabulous first-floor apartment making the most of its elevated status boasting a light-filled interior, finest-quality features and delightful neighbourhood views. Description:
Designer inner-city warehouse living
An exclusive boutique development in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct sets the scene for this New York-style townhouse enjoying absolute privacy, luxury and inner-city practicality. One of only 16 in a serene environment defined by its grand open-roof foyer and bold industrial cues, the townhouse itself boasts one extra-large bedroom (built-in robes) and deluxe ensuite bathroom, gourmet stone-bench kitchen with soft-close drawers and finest appliances, plus a light-filled open living/dining area complete with loft-style study. Vaulted ceilings, exposed beams and solid brickwork add to the appeal, as well as polished hardwood floors, Euro laundry, intercom/secure entry and lower-level parking space. Modern living wrapped in heritage style, Smith Street/Gertrude Street cafes and restaurants, cosmopolitan shopping precincts and city-bound trams are all within easy reach.
